&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Bristol, North Somerset and South Gloucestershire CCG BI team are seeking a data engineer to help support development of the BNSSG System-wide Dataset - a pseudonymised and linked routine health and care database of over one million individuals. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post, which works closely with the BI Modelling and Analytics team, will have responsibility for transforming data feeds received from a range of data providers into linked, structured data marts for onwards analysis. In addition to technical processes, the post-holder will develop and maintain supporting guidance materials for use by a range of customers; proactively work with partners to identify and deliver new data sources; identify and resolve data quality issues; evolve the information governance framework and develop a detailed knowledge of the data to help support analysis.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post offers a unique and exciting opportunity to work in support of a number of analytical projects using this dataset and play a direct role in shaping its future. The post is offered on a fixed-term basis for an 18 month period. Secondments would also be considered for this role. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
